**Overall Meaning:**

The scripture said that the guru is indeed Hari (Lord Vishnu) directly, not another. This verse elevates the guru to the level of the divine, highlighting their importance in the spiritual journey. It emphasizes that the guru is not merely a teacher but a manifestation of the divine, embodying the ultimate truth. 


